Error: `lda (addr)` requires the indirect pointer to be `:word`; var `str_ptr_b` is declared `:byte`
   ╭─[ tests/golden/fixtures/syntax-addrmode-indirect-err-ptr/input.k65:6:5 ]
   │
 6 │     lda (str_ptr_b)
   │     ───────┬───────  
   │            ╰───────── indirect pointer operand
   │ 
   │ Help: declare the pointer as `var str_ptr_b:word = ...` so it can hold a 16-bit zero-page address, or use `[str_ptr_b]` long-indirect if `str_ptr_b` actually holds a 24-bit pointer
   │ 
   │ Note: Direct-page indirect addressing on the W65C816 reads a 16-bit pointer from zero page; the loaded data width is determined by the M flag (the active `@a8`/`@a16` mode), not by the pointer's declared width.
───╯

